# Code Review

## Purpose

Every change is reviewed — even when implementation appears successful.

## Review Flow

```
Review Specialist → checklist + findings
        ↓
Orchestrator → final review + approval decision
```

## Review Categories

| Category | Check |
|----------|-------|
| Correctness | Requirements met; edge cases handled |
| Security | No secrets committed; no XSS/injection vectors |
| Performance | No obvious regressions |
| Maintainability | Clear naming; no dead code |
| Consistency | Matches `20-project-conventions.mdc` and `10-technology-rules.mdc` |
| Regression risk | Existing behavior preserved unless intentional |

## Checklist

- [ ] Requirements satisfied
- [ ] No dead code or unused imports
- [ ] No duplicated logic — reuse `lib/utils.ts`, existing components
- [ ] Naming conventions followed
- [ ] `@/` imports for cross-folder references
- [ ] Section IDs match nav if sections/nav touched
- [ ] `"use client"` only where needed
- [ ] Accessibility preserved
- [ ] `npm run build` passes
- [ ] `npx tsc --noEmit` passes

## Output Format

```
✓ Passed: [items]
✗ Critical: [file:line — issue]
⚠ Advisory: [suggestions]
Evidence: [build/test output]
```

Review Specialist returns findings. **Only Orchestrator approves.**
